<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 10th year of Kōvirājakesarivarman. For Mahādeva of Tiruvālantuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, Nilaiyaṉ Pukaḻaṉ, a shepherd <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>maṉṟāṭi</foreign></supplied> of this village <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivvūr</foreign></supplied>, placed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 60 goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭu</foreign></supplied>. In these <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivaṟṟuḷ</foreign></supplied>, having removed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nīkki</foreign></supplied> 45 goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭu</foreign></supplied> for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āḻakku</foreign> &gt; <foreign>uḻakku</foreign></supplied> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neykku</foreign></supplied> every day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicatam</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> a day-lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pakal viḷakku</foreign></supplied>, 15 goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭu</foreign></supplied> remained <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>niṉṟa</foreign></supplied>; 15 <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s <supplied reason="explanation">?</supplied> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>canay</foreign> &gt; <foreign>ney</foreign></supplied> were placed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> for the sacred bath <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭiyaruḷa</foreign></supplied> on that day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāṉṉṟu</foreign> &gt; <foreign>nāṉṟu</foreign></supplied> of Saṅkirānti falling in Uttaramayaṉam. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras. </p></div>

